<document>
	<title>Glucose intolerance in a three-year-old child with cystic fibrosis.</title>

	<author>Peden-V-H.</author>
	<author>Powell-K-R.</author>
	<author>Rejent-A-J.</author>

	<source>Clin-Pediatr (Phila). 1974 Jan. 13(1). P 10-1 passim.</source>

	<abstract>Glucose intolerance preceding pulmonary disease in a child with
   cystic fibrosis is described.  After glucose intolerance was
   controlled with tolbutamide, the pulmonary infection resolved.
   Early recognition and treatment of &quot;diabetes&quot; in children with
   cystic fibrosis is emphasized.</abstract>

